# {{.Name}}

`{{.Name}}` is a rebrandable devedge CLI shell built on the open-core
[devedge-cli-sdk](https://github.com/infobloxopen/devedge-cli-sdk) `clikit`
runtime. It is the CLI mirror of a devedge micro-frontend shell: the shell owns
session construction (a generic OIDC device-grant provider, or a `--dev` stub)
and composes generated **domain command modules** that consume only the
read-only runtime.

## Layout

- `main.go` — the shell: app wiring, the OIDC session factory, and the doctor
  command.
- `domains_gen.go` — generated wiring that registers each domain module. Managed
  by `de cli add`; do not edit.
- `gen/<domain>/` — one generated domain command module per API. Generated by
  cligen through `de cli add`; do not edit.

## Add a domain

Generate a domain command module from an enriched OpenAPI v3 spec and wire it in:

```
de cli add --input path/to/service.openapi.yaml --domain widgets
go mod tidy
go build -o {{.Name}} .
```

Re-running `de cli add` for a domain regenerates it in place; the wiring in
`domains_gen.go` is idempotent.

## Run

```
./{{.Name}} --help
./{{.Name}} <domain> --help
./{{.Name}} --dev --server http://localhost:8080 <domain> list
```

`--dev` uses a static dev token instead of real auth (development only). For real
auth, configure an OIDC profile in `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/{{.Name}}/config.yaml`:

```yaml
current_profile: default
profiles:
  default:
    server: https://api.example.com
    auth:
      type: oidc
      oidc:
        issuer: https://issuer.example.com
        client_id: your-client-id
```

The app name (`{{.AppName}}`) also derives the env-var prefix, so the server
base URL and profile can be overridden from the environment (for example
`{{.AppName}}`-prefixed `_SERVER` and `_PROFILE` variables).
